Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell[TextData[{
 "PHGN 570: Computational Project 1\n",
 StyleBox["Convolutions",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"]
}], "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7552740620598*^9, 3.755274072243856*^9}, {
  3.755274695714754*^9, 
  3.75527469712357*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"48264375-2681-44fa-89ef-\
d9e6f107159b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Project Summary", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.755274163607428*^9, 
  3.755274166357678*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"836bb4d4-c4d3-46fc-9bab-\
898348d03f11"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Convolutions are an inevitable part of measurements. A good understanding \
of both the concept and working principles of convolutions is necessary for \
all components of STEM.\n\nThe goal of this project is to investigate \
convolutions and their algebraic properties. This project will be completed \
both in theory and computationally using Matlab. ",
 StyleBox["YOU MAY NOT USE MATLAB\[CloseCurlyQuote]s BUILT IN CONV FUNCTION",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7552741528068542`*^9, 3.75527415801682*^9}, {
  3.7552742810456867`*^9, 3.755274291135635*^9}, {3.755274408601207*^9, 
  3.755274418462164*^9}, {3.755274487639176*^9, 3.7552745068734083`*^9}, {
  3.755282155565679*^9, 3.75528222686957*^9}, {3.755282372829183*^9, 
  3.7552823868703613`*^9}, {3.755283771377837*^9, 3.7552837714499607`*^9}, {
  3.755286700300742*^9, 3.755286707074732*^9}, {3.943977721418336*^9, 
  3.943977722878965*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"749fed14-e253-4514-aaac-\
a82b678f4fdc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Deliverable", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.755282425706918*^9, 
  3.7552824275818157`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ba070f3c-e3c8-4db5-9e6e-\
446179b945df"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The deliverable for this project is working code and documentation \
articulating the results. The code must ",
 StyleBox["VISUALLY",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " demonstrate how convolutions work. Students must use Matlab to ",
 StyleBox["computationally",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "and",
 StyleBox[" VISUALLY",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " demonstrate the convolution between the following real-valued functions:\n\
\n1. Rectangle (HeavisidePi, UnitBox)\n2. Isosceles triangle (UnitTriangle)\n\
3. Right triangle\n4. Causally ",
 StyleBox["decreasing",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " exponential function\n\nThis requires 6 ",
 StyleBox["animations",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". ",
 StyleBox["YOU MAY NOT USE MATLAB\[CloseCurlyQuote]s BUILT IN CONV FUNCTION \
(or any variant thereof)",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". You MUST use loops to calculate all quantities displayed in the \
animation.\n\nStudents have the freedom to choose how the animations are \
presented. Because I will be running the code to make sure it works, students \
may choose to simply provide detailed instructions on how to run the code in \
order to produce each animation.\n\nAn example animation is included in the \
next cell:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.755282429783079*^9, 3.755282500456934*^9}, {
  3.755282636655736*^9, 3.755282786784939*^9}, {3.7552830011006413`*^9, 
  3.7552830052244883`*^9}, {3.755283221339746*^9, 3.755283222498693*^9}, {
  3.755283280625964*^9, 3.75528333427464*^9}, {3.755283379194358*^9, 
  3.755283639534164*^9}, {3.755283720875433*^9, 3.7552837491119757`*^9}, {
  3.755283812849745*^9, 3.755283875915708*^9}, {3.755283929696662*^9, 
  3.755284008097831*^9}, {3.7552846136606083`*^9, 3.7552846159527082`*^9}, {
  3.755285121301711*^9, 3.755285122877103*^9}, {3.7552863971727533`*^9, 
  3.7552864076890697`*^9}, {3.75528680200073*^9, 3.7552868025092688`*^9}, {
  3.7552869628707447`*^9, 3.755286972008945*^9}, {3.943977473460537*^9, 
